data.title: What a difference a year makes
data.text: Last year i reviewed the Panariellos and gave it 5 stars.  Being away for the summer we were anxious to go back.  We were so disappointed!  The start to waiter was coughing all over us, he said he had a sore throat. Three of us ordered pasta that came in a bowl with the sauce on top not mixed in. The Alfredo I had looked thick and over rich, it was.  The others had a tomato sauce that had a rusty taste.  The fourth had a pizza, he was happy

data.title: Authentic Italian
data.text: This is a new location. We were very pleased. Being from NJ, we were looking for good Italian food. There was a couple having pizza which looked great. We ordered the eggplant Parmesan and eggplant rollatini. Both came with nice salads and spaghetti. The free garlic rolls were delicious. We had more than enough leftover for another meal. Highly recommend. Great service, the waitress Sunny was very friendly.
